               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipit of Text I and its sections; incipits of Texts II-VI; incipit of the articles in Text I; initial word of the sections of Texts III, V and VI; abbreviations referring to other works in Text I; numbers of the articles in Text I; numbers in the introduction, in the index and in the articles of Text I; words mәʿәraf “chapter” and kәfәl “section” in Text I; words ʾanqäṣ “section”, säʾәlät “question” and kәfәl “section” in Text II; directive to the ministers in Text II; abbreviations of the directives yәbәl kahәn “the priest says”, yәbәl diyaqon “the deacon says”, yәbәl ḥәzb “the people say” in Text II; numbering of the sections of Text V; words ḥatäta “question” and fәkkare “explanation” in Text V; the verbal form ʾәmbo “if there is…” in Text VI;  Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs. &#xD;
On fols. 2r, 174r, a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
